Today is a day to educate one another on this history and seek the resources to continue learning what isn't being taught in our education systems. 

Truth and Reconciliation Day or Orange shirt day is a day to honour and remember the survivors and children who never made it home from the Residential schools in both the US and Canada. These schools were created to eliminate us as a People with the ultimate goal to separate our children from our communities, culture and heritage and erase our way of life and being as Indigenous people from existence.

We honour the survivors of these abusive schools and those who never returned. We are grateful everyday to be able to continue to express our identities as Ogwehonwe and for all Indigenous People to practice our traditions, revitalize our languages and amplify our stories. 

Music by: @antoinexmusic 
Videography by: @jessekochanka
